The paper discusses a machine learning model (Multithreshold Entropy Linear Classifier) and proposes methods to speed up its optimization. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses adaptive schemes for selecting parameters, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization methods discussed involve conjugate gradients and L-BFGS, which are commonly used in optimization problems and fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
